M||tx|---
M||name|fi-based-pricing-advisor
M||desc|>-
M||tx|Evaluate pricing changes using ARPU, conversion, churn risk, NRR, and payback. Use when deciding whether a pricing move shd ship.
M||vers|1.0.0
M||plat|[]
M||meta|
M||herm|
M||tags|[fi, pl, runway, cac, ltv, mrr, margin, roi]
M||inte|Evaluate the **financial impact** of pricing changes (price increases, new tiers, add-ons, discounts) using ARPU/ARPA al, conversion impact, churn risk, NRR effects, and CAC payback implications. Use this to make data-driven go/no-go decisions on proposed pricing changes w/ supporting math and risk assessment.
M||tp|interactive
M||best|
M||scen|
M||tx|---
M|Purp|tx|Evaluate the **financial impact** of pricing changes (price increases, new tiers, add-ons, discounts) using ARPU/ARPA al, conversion impact, churn risk, NRR effects, and CAC payback implications. Use this to make data-driven go/no-go decisions on proposed pricing changes w/ supporting math and risk assessment.
M|Purp|**Wh|** Financial impact evaluation for pricing decisions you're already considering.
M|Purp|**Wh|** Comprehensive pricing st ds, value-based pricing frameworks, willingness-to-pay research, competitive positioning, psychological pricing, packaging architecture, or monetization md selection. For those topics, see the future `pricing-st-suite` skills.
M|Purp|tx|This skill assumes you have a specific pricing change in mind and need to evaluate its financial viability.
M|The |A sy|
M|The |tx|1. **rv Impact** — How does this change ARPU/ARPA?
M|The |it|Direct rv lift from price increase
M|The |it|rv loss from reduced conversion or increased churn
M|The |it|Net rv impact
M|The |tx|2. **Conversion Impact** — How does this affect trial-to-paid or sales conversion?
M|The |it|Higher prices may reduce conversion rate
M|The |it|Better packaging may improve conversion
M|The |it|tst assumptions
M|The |tx|3. **Churn Risk** — Will existing cs leave due to price change?
M|The |it|Grandfathering st (protect existing cs)
M|The |it|Churn risk by segment (SMB vs. enterprise)
M|The |it|Churn elasticity (how sensitive are cs to price?)
M|The |tx|4. **Expansion Impact** — Does this cr or block expansion opportunities?
M|The |it|New premium tier = upsell path
M|The |it|Usage-based pricing = expansion as cs grow
M|The |it|Add-ons = cross-sell opportunities
M|The |tx|5. **CAC Payback Impact** — Does pricing change affect unit economics?
M|The |it|Higher ARPU = faster payback
M|The |it|Lower conversion = higher effective CAC
M|The |- Ne|CAC ratio
M|Pric|**Di|**
M|Pric|it|Price increase (raise prices for all cs or new cs only)
M|Pric|it|New premium tier (cr upsell path)
M|Pric|it|Paid add-on (monetize previously free feature)
M|Pric|it|Usage-based pricing (charge for consumption)
M|Pric|**Di|**
M|Pric|it|Annual prepay discount (improve cash flow)
M|Pric|it|Volume discounts (larger deals)
M|Pric|it|Promotional pricing (temporary price reduction)
M|Pric|**Pa|**
M|Pric|it|Feature bundling (combine features into tiers)
M|Pric|it|Unbundling (separate features into add-ons)
M|Pric|it|Pricing metric change (seats → usage, or vice versa)
M|Anti|- **|** This evaluates a proposed change, not "what shd we charge?"
M|Anti|- **|** This analyzes impact, not "what will cs pay?"
M|Anti|- **|** This is financial al, not mk positioning
M|Anti|- **|** This evaluates one change, not redesigning all tiers
M|When|**Us|**
M|When|it|You have a specific pricing change to evaluate (e.g., "shd we raise prices 20%?")
M|When|it|You need to quantify rv, churn, and conversion trade-offs
M|When|it|You're deciding btw pricing change options (tst A vs. B)
M|When|it|You need to present pricing change impact to leadership or board
M|When|**Do|**
M|When|it|You're designing pricing st from scratch (use value-based pricing frameworks)
M|When|it|You haven't validated willingness-to-pay (do cs research first)
M|When|it|You don't have baseline metrics (ARPU, churn, conversion rates)
M|When|it|Change is too small to matter (<5% price change, <10% of cs affected)
M|When|tx|---
M|Faci|tx|Use [`workshop-facilitation`](../workshop-facilitation/SKILL.md) as the default interaction protocol for this skill.
M|Faci|It d|
M|Faci|it|sn heads-up + entry mode (Guided, Context dump, Best guess)
M|Faci|it|one-question turns w/ plain-language pm
M|Faci|it|progress labels (for example, Context Qx/8 and Scoring Qx/5)
M|Faci|it|interruption handling and pause/resume behavior
M|Faci|it|numbered recommendations at decision points
M|Faci|it|quick-select numbered rp options for regular questions (include `Other (specify)` when useful)
M|Faci|tx|This file defines the domain-specific assessment cn. If there is a conflict, follow this file's domain logic.
