M|Pitf|**Sy|** "We'll raise prices 30% and make $X more!" (no churn modeling)
M|Pitf|**Co|** Churn wipes out rv gains. Net impact negative.
M|Pitf|fix|** md churn scenarios (conservative, base, optimistic). Factor churn-driven rv loss into net impact.
M|Pitf|tx|---
M|Pitf|**Sy|** "We're raising prices for everyone effective immediately"
M|Pitf|**Co|** Massive churn spike from existing cs who feel betrayed.
M|Pitf|fix|** Grandfather existing cs. Raise prices for new cs only.
M|Pitf|tx|---
M|Pitf|**Sy|** "We tested on 10 cs and it worked!"
M|Pitf|**Co|** 10 cs isn't statistically sig. Results are noise.
M|Pitf|fix|** tst w/ large enough sample (100+ cs per cohort) for 60-90 days.
M|Pitf|tx|---
M|Pitf|**Sy|** "We're raising prices bc we need more rv"
M|Pitf|**Co|** cs see price increase w/o corresponding value increase. Churn.
M|Pitf|fix|** Tie price increases to value improvements (new features, better support, outcomes delivered).
M|Pitf|tx|---
M|Pitf|**Sy|** "Higher ARPU is always better!"
M|Pitf|**Co|** If conversion drops 30%, effective CAC increases dramatically. Payback period explodes.
M|Pitf|fix|** Calculate CAC payback impact. Higher ARPU w/ lower conversion might make payback worse, not better.
M|Pitf|tx|---
M|Pitf|**Sy|** "30% discount for annual prepay!" (improves cash but destroys LTV)
M|Pitf|**Co|** cs lock in lo prices for a year. rv per cs decreases.
M|Pitf|fix|** Limit annual discounts to 10-15%. Balance cash flow improvement w/ LTV protection.
M|Pitf|tx|---
M|Pitf|**Sy|** "cr raised prices, so shd we"
M|Pitf|**Co|** Your cs, value prop, and cost structure are different. What works for them may not work for you.
M|Pitf|fix|** Use cr as data points, not decisions. Make pricing decisions based on your unit economics.
M|Pitf|tx|---
M|Pitf|**Sy|** "Let's A/B tst 47 different price points!"
M|Pitf|**Co|** al paralysis. Spending months on 5% pricing optimizations while missing 50% growth opportunities elsewhere.
M|Pitf|fix|** Big pricing changes (tiers, packaging, add-ons) matter more than micro-optimizations. Start there.
M|Pitf|tx|---
M|Pitf|**Sy|** "We're maximizing ARPU at acquisition"
M|Pitf|**Co|** hi upfront pricing prevents landing cs. Miss expansion opportunities.
M|Pitf|fix|** Consider "land and expand" st. Lower entry price, higher expansion rv via upsells.
M|Pitf|tx|---
M|Pitf|**Sy|** "We're raising prices nx month" (no cs communication)
M|Pitf|**Co|** Surprised cs churn. Poor reviews. Reputation damage.
M|Pitf|fix|** Communicate pricing changes 30-60 days in advance. Emphasize value, not just price.
M|Pitf|tx|---
